# OS Init

Script for installing macOS applications from the json file. Constant APPS should be used to change the default path.

## Getting Started

```shell
go run install-apps.go \
  -file macos-reinstall-apps.json \
  -dry-run
```

```shell
go run install-apps.go \
  -file macos-reinstall-apps.json \
  -continue-on-error
```

## The program

- Handles Homebrew formulae and casks
- Installs mas when required
- Installs Mac App Store applications
- Reports manual/vendor installations
- Supports -dry-run and -methods
- Handles interruption signals
- Continues after failures when requested
- It compiled successfully, passed go vet, and processed all 66 entries in a dry run. Sign into the Mac App Store before running the real installation.
